<html>
  <head>
    <title>uncontext.</title>
    <link href="/css/site.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css"/>
    {{#assets.css}}<script src="/css/{{dataset}}/{{slug}}.css"></script>{{/assets.css}}
  </head>
  <body>
    <section id="wrapper">
      <header>
        <h1>Uncontext.</h1>
        <h2>What could be greater than golf with a gator?</h2>
      </header>

      <div class="intro">
        <p>So what&rsquo;s the fucking deal with shit anyway. Can&rsquo;t help but notice that certain things are a certain way. My expecatations were that things might be a different way. Anyway, that&rsquo;s the rub I guess. Things are ways.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="two-up">
        <div class="data-group">
          <h3>Data for this session: literature</h3>
           <div class="data">
             <table>
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <td>a</td>
                  <td>b</td>
                  <td>c</td>
                  <td>d</td>
                  <td>e</td>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
              </tbody>
             </table>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="canvas-group">
          <h3>A visualization might look like this</h3>
          <canvas id="homepage-canvas" width="400px" height="400px"></canvas>
          <div class="explanation">
            <ul>
              <li>When data.a is updated, a new line of circle is initiated, with that number of circles spaced along the y-axis.</li>
              <li>The size that the circles grows to is whatever data.b is at the time.</li>
              <li>If data.c === 0, the circles expand towards the right. If data.c === 1, then it's left.</li>
              <li>data.e.f / data.e.g determines the percentage along the x-axis the line runs along.</li>
              <li>Where's data.d? We don't need to use everything, silly.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
        
      {{#datasets}}
      <h3>{{name}}</h3>
      <ul class="scenes">
      {{#slugs}}
        <li class="scene"><a href="/{{name}}/{{.}}">{{.}}</a></li>
      {{/slugs}}
      </ul>
      <div class="clear"></div>
      {{/datasets}}

    </section>

    <script src="/js/vendor/jquery-1.11.0.min.js"></script>
    {{#assets.threejs}}<script src='/js/vendor/three-r67.min.js'></script>
    <script src="/fonts/helvetiker_regular.typeface.js"></script>
    <script src="/js/vendor/CSS3DRenderer.min.js"></script>{{/assets.threejs}}
    {{#assets.processing}}<script src='/js/vendor/processing-1.4.8.min.js'></script>{{/assets.processing}}
    {{#assets.raphael}}<script src='/js/vendor/raphael-2.1.2.min.js'></script>{{/assets.raphael}}
    {{#assets.toxiclibs}}<script src='/js/vendor/toxiclibs-0.2.7.min.js'></script>{{/assets.toxiclibs}}
    <script src="/socket.io/socket.io.js"></script>
    <script src="/js/site.js"></script>
    <script src="/js/homepage.js"></script>
    {{#assets.js}}<script src="/js/{{dataset}}/{{slug}}.js"></script>{{/assets.js}}
    <script src="/js/analytics.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>